MICROWAVE
MEASUREMENTS
ON
A
HIGH
FREQUENCY
EXCITED
GAS
DISCHARGE
WAVES
WERE
TRANSMITTED
THROUGH
THE
DISCHARGE
VESSEL
AND
AMPLITUDE
AND
PHASE
CHANGES
WERE
MEASURED
AS
A
FUNCTION
OF
THE
ANODE
VOLTAGE
OF
THE
PLASMA
PRODUCING
HF
GENERATOR
HORN
RADIATORS
WERE
APPLIED
TO
THE
ENDS
OR
SIDES
OF
THE
VESSEL
AND
THE
DIRECTION
OF
POLARIZATION
WAS
VARIED
